<docs>
	<doc for="DataColumnChangeEventHandler">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents the method that will handle the <see cref="System.Data.DataTable.ColumnChanging"/> event.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="sender">The source of the event.</param>
		<param name="e">A <see cref="System.Data.DataColumnChangeEventArgs"/> that contains the event data.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para>When you create a <see cref="System.Data.DataColumnChangeEventHandler"/> delegate, you identify
   the method that will handle the event. To associate the event with your
   event handler, add an instance of the delegate to the event. The
   event handler is called whenever the event occurs, until you remove the
   delegate. For more information about delegates, see <see topic="cpconEventsDelegates"/>.</para>
			<note type="note">
   The declaration of your
   event handler must have the same parameters as the
<see langword="DataColumnChangeEventHandler"/> delegate 
   declaration.
</note>
		</remarks>
		<seealso cref="System.Data.DataColumn"/>
	</doc>
</docs>
